# Kactus - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Python monorepo for financial data collection, processing, and serving. It uses uv workspaces with three packages that share a common library.

## Project Structure
- `packages/kactus-common/` - Shared library (DuckDB client, Pydantic schemas, constants)
  - `src/kactus_common/database/` - DatabaseClient, Column, Table, DataType, UpdateStrategy
  - `src/kactus_common/schemas/` - Shared Pydantic models (SyncDataResponse)
- `packages/kactus-data/` - Data scraping, collection, ETL pipelines
  - `src/kactus_data/sources/` - DataSource ABC and provider implementations
  - `src/kactus_data/jobs/` - Scheduled ETL jobs
- `packages/kactus-fin/` - FastAPI backend server
  - `src/kactus_fin/app.py` - FastAPI app factory
  - `src/kactus_fin/config.py` - Pydantic Settings
  - `src/kactus_fin/api/` - API route definitions

## Python Coding Standards

### General Guidelines
- Always answer in English
- Use Python 3.12 features
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use type hints for all functions and class methods
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Add docstrings for all classes and public methods

### Import Conventions
- Shared code lives in `kactus_common` — import from there, not between kactus-data and kactus-fin
- Use `from kactus_common.database.client import DatabaseClient` (not relative imports across packages)
- Use `from kactus_common.schemas.data_source import SyncDataResponse` for shared models

### Package Management
- Use `uv` for dependency management
- Add package-specific deps to the correct `packages/*/pyproject.toml`
- Shared deps go in `kactus-common`
- Run `uv sync --all-packages` after adding deps
